body:
# Stripe Subscriptions

Subscriptions automate recurring billing by tying a customer to one or more prices on a schedule. Stripe handles invoice generation, payment collection, retry logic, and lifecycle events. You will need a `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` from your [[stripe]] dashboard.

## Create a Subscription

```javascript
import Stripe from 'stripe';
const stripe = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY);

const subscription = await stripe.subscriptions.create({
  customer: 'cus_xxx',
  items: [{ price: 'price_xxx' }],
  trial_period_days: 14,
  metadata: { plan: 'pro' },
});

console.log(subscription.id);                  // sub_xxx
console.log(subscription.status);              // 'trialing' or 'active'
console.log(subscription.current_period_end);  // Unix timestamp
```

## Products and Prices

Products describe what you sell. Prices define how much and how often:

```javascript
// Create a product
const product = await stripe.products.create({
  name: 'Pro Plan',
  description: 'Full access to all features',
});

// Create a recurring price
const price = await stripe.prices.create({
  product: product.id,
  unit_amount: 2999,       // $29.99
  currency: 'usd',
  recurring: { interval: 'month' },
});

// Tiered pricing
const tieredPrice = await stripe.prices.create({
  product: product.id,
  currency: 'usd',
  billing_scheme: 'tiered',
  tiers_mode: 'graduated',
  tiers: [
    { up_to: 100, unit_amount: 10 },    // First 100 units at $0.10
    { up_to: 'inf', unit_amount: 5 },    // Rest at $0.05
  ],
  recurring: { interval: 'month' },
});
```

## Trial Periods

Trials delay the first charge:

```javascript
// On subscription creation
const sub = await stripe.subscriptions.create({
  customer: 'cus_xxx',
  items: [{ price: 'price_xxx' }],
  trial_period_days: 14,
  // OR: trial_end: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 30 * 86400,
});
// sub.status === 'trialing'
// Listen for 'customer.subscription.trial_will_end' via [[stripe/webhooks]]
```

## Upgrades and Downgrades

Switch prices with proration:

```javascript
const subscription = await stripe.subscriptions.retrieve('sub_xxx');

await stripe.subscriptions.update('sub_xxx', {
  items: [{
    id: subscription.items.data[0].id,
    price: 'price_new_xxx',  // New price ID
  }],
  proration_behavior: 'create_prorations',  // or 'none', 'always_invoice'
});
```

## Cancellation

```javascript
// Cancel at period end (customer keeps access until then)
await stripe.subscriptions.update('sub_xxx', {
  cancel_at_period_end: true,
});

// Cancel immediately
await stripe.subscriptions.cancel('sub_xxx');
```

Listen for `customer.subscription.deleted` via [[stripe/webhooks]] to handle post-cancellation cleanup.

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Server-side API key (`sk_test_...` or `sk_live_...`) |
